    <!-- 4. Typography -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="eyebrow">TYPOGRAPHY</div>
      <h2 class="font-heading">Outfit display + Inter body + JetBrains Mono</h2>
      <p class="desc">Outfit (700/800) carries headings and the wordmark; Inter (400/500/600) handles body and UI; JetBrains Mono stays for code and type badges. Tight letter-spacing (<code class="font-mono">-0.02em</code>) on display sizes.</p>
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem;">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">DISPLAY · OUTFIT 700</div>
          <div class="font-heading" style="font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1; color: var(--soil-900);">Browse any VGI catalog.</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">H2 · OUTFIT 600</div>
          <div class="font-heading" style="font-size: 1.875rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.01em; color: var(--soil-900);">Schemas in albemarle_gis</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">BODY · INTER 400</div>
          <div style="font-size: 1rem; color: var(--soil-700); max-width: 60ch; line-height: 1.6;">Connect to a VGI server, drill into tables and views, run SQL via the embedded DuckDB shell, or hand the schema to the AI analyst to draft a query.</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">MONO · JETBRAINS 400</div>
          <code class="font-mono" style="display:inline-block; padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; background:#fff; border:1px solid var(--soil-200); border-radius: 0.375rem; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--soil-800);">SELECT * FROM property.parcels ORDER BY rowid LIMIT 50;</code>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 5. Buttons -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="eyebrow">BUTTONS</div>
      <h2 class="font-heading">Harvest for action, earth for chrome</h2>
      <p class="desc">Primary actions (Connect, Run, Retry) take harvest-500; chrome buttons like "Open SQL Shell" use earth-600. Outline + ghost handle secondary affordances. Focus rings shift to harvest-500.</p>
      <div style="display:flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center;">
        <button class="btn btn-primary">Primary · harvest-500</button>
        <button class="btn btn-earth">Earth chrome</button>
        <button class="btn btn-outline">Outline</button>
        <button class="btn btn-ghost">Ghost</button>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 6. Cards -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="eyebrow">CARDS</div>
      <h2 class="font-heading">Default + featured variants</h2>
      <p class="desc">Default cards keep VGI's subtle ring border. The featured variant (used on the ConnectBox and empty states) gains an earth-50 wash with a 2px earth-300 ring + soft shadow — echoes the marketing site's hero cards.</p>
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem;">
        <div class="bp-card">
          <h3>Schema · property</h3>
          <p>6 tables · 1 view. Updated 4 hours ago. Current county property parcels and improvements.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bp-card featured">
          <h3>Connect to a VGI server</h3>
          <p>Paste a server URL to begin. Recently used: <span class="font-mono" style="font-size:0.875rem; color: var(--earth-700);">http://localhost:9003</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 7. Sidebar tree -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="eyebrow">SIDEBAR · SELECTION</div>
      <h2 class="font-heading">Selected items go harvest</h2>
      <p class="desc">Tree selection moves from forest-green at 15% to harvest-100 with a harvest-500 left rail — brighter, more clearly "active", and family-aligned. Hover stays the same neutral soil-100 wash.</p>
      <div class="bp-tree">
        <div class="row"><span class="icon">📁</span> districts</div>
        <div class="row"><span class="icon">📁</span> environment</div>
        <div class="row" style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--soil-900);"><span class="icon">📂</span> property</div>
        <div style="padding-left: 1.5rem;">
          <div class="row"><span class="icon">▦</span> card_level_data</div>
          <div class="row"><span class="icon">▦</span> county_parcels</div>
          <div class="row selected"><span class="icon">▦</span> parcels <span class="badge bp-b-string">VARCHAR</span></div>
          <div class="row"><span class="icon">▦</span> parcel_info</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 8. Type badges -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="eyebrow">TYPE BADGES</div>
      <h2 class="font-heading">Retoned strings + booleans</h2>
      <p class="desc">String types adopt the harvest scale; booleans take the new duck yellow. Integer/float blues, date purples, and the geometry orange stay — those colors carry information rather than branding and stay legible against the new defaults.</p>
      <div>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-string">VARCHAR</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-string">TEXT</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-string">JSON</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-int">INTEGER</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-int">BIGINT</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-float">DOUBLE</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-float">DECIMAL</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-bool">BOOLEAN</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-date">DATE</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-ts">TIMESTAMP</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-uuid">UUID</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-geom">GEOMETRY</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-geom">WKB</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-struct">STRUCT</span>
        <span class="bp-badge bp-b-struct">LIST</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 9. Before / After comparison -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="eyebrow">SIDE BY SIDE</div>
      <h2 class="font-heading">Before vs after</h2>
      <p class="desc">A direct comparison so you can decide whether the warm-earth direction reads better against the existing app. Same content, different palette.</p>
      <div class="bp-compare">
        <div class="bp-compare-col before">
          <div class="label">CURRENT · VGI green</div>
          <div class="bp-old-card">
            <h3 style="font-family: Inter, sans-serif;">Schema · property</h3>
            <p style="color:#2c2c1e; margin:0;">6 tables · 1 view.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bp-old-btn">Open SQL Shell</div>
          <div class="bp-tree" style="border-color:#f0ece0; background:#fff;">
            <div class="row" style="color:#2c2c1e;"><span class="icon" style="color:#2d5016;">📂</span> property</div>
            <div class="row bp-old-row selected" style="padding-left:0.5rem;"><span class="icon" style="color:#2d5016;">▦</span> parcels</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bp-compare-col after">
          <div class="label">PROPOSED · Query.Farm aligned</div>
          <div class="bp-card">
            <h3>Schema · property</h3>
            <p style="margin:0;">6 tables · 1 view.</p>
          </div>
          <button class="btn btn-earth">Open SQL Shell</button>
          <div class="bp-tree">
            <div class="row" style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--soil-900);"><span class="icon">📂</span> property</div>
            <div class="row selected"><span class="icon">▦</span> parcels</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer style="background: var(--soil-900); color: var(--soil-200); padding: 2rem 1.5rem; text-align: center; font-size: 0.875rem;">
      <div style="font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">🚜 Query.Farm</div>
      <div style="color: var(--soil-400);">Brand preview · not a live mockup of the catalog browser</div>
    </footer>

  </body>
